-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimpact%20American%20businesses%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20demand%20for%20consulting%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndustry%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider%20they%20expect%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-white-house-staff-cabinet-picks-list-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump's%20election%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20increase%20demand%20for%20consulting%2C%20including%20strategy%2C%20management%2C%20reorganizational%2C%20and%20technical%20advisory%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20election%20of%20Trump%20is%20very%20favorable%20for%20the%20consulting%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20Michael%20Mische%2C%20a%20management%20consultant%2C%20former%20partner%20at%20KPMG%2C%20and%20professor%20at%20USC's%20Marshall%20School%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMische%20said%20the%20primary%20factors%20that%20drive%20consulting%20are%20typically%20macroeconomic%20health%2C%20government%20spending%2C%20CEO%20sentiment%2C%20free%20cash%20flows%2C%20and%20client%20need.%20He%20said%20there%20has%20been%20client%20need%20over%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20but%20some%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3ECEOs%20have%20been%20hesitant%20to%20act%20on%20it%20due%20to%20a%20tough%20macroeconomic%20environment%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20industry%20is%20highly%20vulnerable%20and%20elastic%20depending%20on%20what's%20going%20on%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20entire%20consulting%20industry%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20predicated%20on%20the%20fact%20that%20it's%20the%20discretionary%20item.%20It%20literally%20is%20the%20luxury%20item%20of%20the%20CEO%2C%26quot%3B%20Mische%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20accounting%20or%20legal%20services%2C%20consultants%20are%20not%20a%20must-have%2C%20and%20they%20are%20quick%20to%20go%20when%20CEO%20sentiment%20is%20down%20or%20economic%20outlooks%20are%20uncertain.%20But%20Mische%20said%20Trump's%20election%20will