s%20will%20trigger%20an%20economic%20downturn.%20With%20inflation%20still%20running%20hot%2C%20that%20could%20create%20a%20nightmare%20outcome%20for%20Kremlin%20officials%3A%20stagflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20result%20of%20the%20central%20bank's%20actions%2C%20the%20Russian%20economy%20is%20effectively%20facing%20the%20threat%20of%20stagflation%20%E2%80%94%20simultaneous%20stagnation%20or%20even%20recession%20and%20high%20inflation%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20government%20advising%20think%20tank%20said%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fpro-government-economists-blame-central-bank-plunging-russia-into-stagflation-2024-11-13%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etranslated%20by%20Reuters%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20scenario%2C%20where%20growth%20is%20low%20and%20inflation%20high%2C%20is%20most%20feared%20by%20any%20central%20bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStagflation%20is%20harder%20to%20escape%20than%20a%20recession.%20When%20an%20economy%20typically%20slows%20down%2C%20central%20banks%20can%20loosen%20interest%20rates%20to%20revive%20activity.%20But%20that%20option%20disappears%20if%20inflation%20keeps%20rising%3A%20interest%20rates%20must%20stay%20high%20to%20cool%20price%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPut%20simply%2C%20the%20Kremlin's%20hands%20appear%20to%20be%20tied.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20central%20bank%20has%20already%20sensed%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-economy-outlook-stagflation-recession-inflation-gdp-growth-ukraine-war-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elooming%20risk%20of%20stagflation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20citing%20that%20price%20growth%20remained%20stubbornly%20high%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%202024%20despite%20cooling%20domestic%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20that%20end%2C%20the%20bank%20elected%20to%20raise%20Russia's%20key%20interest%20rate%20to%20a%20record%20high%20of%2021%25%20last%20month%2C%20and%20indicated%20more%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C