dent%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%20has%20told%20House%20Republicans%20that%20he%20might%20consider%20a%20constitution-breaking%20third%20term%20in%20office.%20President-elect%20Trump%2C%20who%20has%20a%20penchant%20for%20making%20controversial%20statements%2C%20said%20%26quot%3BI%20suspect%20I%20won't%20be%20running%20again%20unless%20you%20(supporters)%20say%20otherwise%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20speech%20to%20fellow%20Republicans%20elected%20to%20the%20House%20of%20Representatives%2C%20Mr%20Trump%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20suspect%20I%20won't%20be%20running%20again%20unless%20you%20say%2C%20'He's%20good%2C%20we%20got%20to%20figure%20something%20else'.%26quot%3B%20His%20statement%20at%20a%20hotel%20in%20Washington%20DC%20ahead%20of%20his%20meeting%20with%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20was%20cheered%20by%20his%20supporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20common%20knowledge%20that%20there%20are%20provisions%20in%20place%20in%20the%20US%20Constitution%20which%20restricts%20a%20US%20President%20from%20standing%20for%20re-election%20for%20a%20third%20term%2C%20but%20how%20safe%20are%20those%20safeguards%3F%20Here's%20a%20look%20at%20whether%20Donald%20Trump%20can%20run%20again%20for%20presidency%20in%202028.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2022nd%20Amendment%20of%20the%20United%20States%20Constitution%20stops%20any%20President%20from%20running%20for%20a%20third%20term%2C%20so%20if%20Donald%20Trump%20wants%20to%20seek%20a%20third%20term%2C%20he%20will%20first%20have%20to%20scrap%20that%20amendment.%20Doing%20so%20is%20a%20daunting%20task%20as%20it%20requires%20the%20President%20to%20garner%20an%20overwhelming%20amount%20of%20support%20from%20Congress%20as%20well%20as%20state%20legislatures.%20This%20is%20something%20that%20Trump%20is%20unlikely%20to%20be%20able%20to%20achieve.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20an%20article%20in%20US-based%20news%20website%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20follow%2C%20no%20index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2Fpolitics%2F383616%2Ftrump-third-term-constitution-22nd-amendment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVox%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20interviewed%20a%20law%20professor%20from%20Stanford%20University%20who%20specialises%20in%20constitutional%20interpretation%2C%20a%20question%20about%20the%20possibility%20of%20such%20a%20Constitutional%20amendment%20was%20asked.%20His%20reply%20was%20clear%20-%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%20there%20are%20none.%20This%20will%20be%20his%20last%20run%20for%20President%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20law%20professor%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWHAT%20IS%20THE%2022nd%20AMENDMENT%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2022nd%20Amendment%20of%20the%20US%20Constitution%20says%20that%20a%20President%20can%20have%20two%20terms%20in%20office%20and%20no%20further.%20It%20is%20applicable%20to%20Presidents%2C%20both%20in%20consecutive%20and%20non-consecutive%20terms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Section%201%20of%20the%2022nd%20Amendment%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%20%26quot%3BNo%20person%20shall%20be%20elected%20to%20the%20office%20of%20the%20President%20more%20than%20twice%2C%20and%20no%20person%20who%20has%20held%20the%20office%20of%20President%2C%20or%20acted%20as%20President%2C%20for%20more%20than%20two%20years%20of%20a%20term%20to%20which%20some%20other%20person%20was%20elected%20President%20shall%20be%20elected%20to%20the%20office%20of%20the%20President%20more%20than%20once.%20But%20this%20Article%20shall%20not%20apply%20to%20any%20person%20holding%20the%20office%20of%20President%20when%20this%20Article%20was%20proposed%20by%20the%20Congress%2C%20and%20shall%20not%20prevent%20any%20person%20who%20may%20be%20holding%20the%20office%20of%20President%2C%20or%20acting%20as%20President%2C%20during%20the%20term%20within%20which%20this%20Article%20becomes%20operative%20from%20holding%20the%20office%20of%20President%20or%20acting%20as%20President%20during%20the%20remainder%20of%20such%20term.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Section%202%20states%20that%20%26quot%3BThis%20article%20shall%20be%20inoperative%20unless%20it%20shall%20have%20been%20ratified%20as%20an%20amendment%20to%20the%20Constitution%20by%20the%20legislatures%20of%20three-fourths%20of%20the%20several%20States%20within%20seven%20years%20from%20the%20date%20of%20its%20submission%20to%20the%20States%20by%20the%20Congress.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHISTORY%20OF%20THE%2022nd%20AMENDMENT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20provision%20to%20restrict%20US%20Presidents%20strictly%20to%20a%20maximum%20of%20two%20terms%20first%20came%20into%20force%20in%201951%2C%20when%20both%20Republicans%20and%20Democrats%20had%20demanded%20for%20such%20a%20provision%20to%20be%20in%20place.%20This%20was%20because%20former%20US%20President%20Franklin%20D%20Roosevelt%20was%20elected%20to%20the%20highest%20office%20for%20an%20unprecedented%20four%20times.%20In%201945%2C%20he%20had%20died%20in%20office%20during%20his%20fourth%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20Roosevelt%20was%20the%20only%20President%20to%20be%20elected%20more%20than%20two%20times%2C%20American%20lawmakers%20from%20both%20parties%20had%20decided%20that%20the%20presidential%20terms%20must%20have%20a%20ceiling%20limit%2C%20and%20hence%20the%2022nd%20Amendment%20came%20into%20force%2C%20restricting%20all%20Presidents%20then%20on%20to%20a%20maximum%20of%20two%20terms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20US's%20first%20President%20and%20founding%20father%20George%20Washington%20had%20served%20for%20a%20maximum%20of%20two%20terms%2C%20both%20parties%20agreed%20that%20this%20was%20the%20legacy%20to%20be%20followed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ECAN%20AN%20AMENDMENT%20IN%20THE%20US%20CONSTITUTION%20BE%20REPEALED%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20checks%20and%20balances%20in%20place%20to%20ensure%20that%20an%20Amendment%20to%20the%20Constitution%20is%20not%20easily%20repealed%20are%20watertight.%20It%20dissuades%20and%20discourages%20amendments%20from%20being%20scrapped%20or%20repealed.%20However%2C%20it%20is%20not%20impossible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20do%20so%2C%20a%20bill%20for%20such%20order%20would%20have%20to%20be%20agreed%20to%20by%20two-thirds%20majority%20(67%20per%20cent)%20of%20both%20the%20House%20and%20the%20Senate.%20The%20House%20of%20Representatives%20has%20435%20members%2C%20of%20which%20290%20must%20vote%20for%20such%20a%20revocation.%20Similarly%2C%20in%20the%20Senate%2C%20which%20has%20100%20members%2C%2067%20must%20agree%20with%20it.%20That%20is%20not%20all.%20Should%20a%20bill%20be%20passed%20by%20the%20House%20and%20the%20Senate%2C%20it%20then%20goes%20to%20each%20of%20the%20states%20-%20which%20need%20to%20pass%20it%20with%20a%20three-fourths%20majority%2C%20and%20since%20the%20United%20States%20of%20America%20are%2050%20states%2C%2038%20of%20them%20would%20have%20to%20agree%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20safe%20to%20assume%20that%20to%20cross%20all%20three%20hurdles%20would%20be%20highly%20unlikely%20for%20Donald%20Trump.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731517920000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2F1oqbsaio_donald-trump-reuters_625x300_06_November_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-talks-of-constitution-breaking-3rd-term-as-president-details-here-7012449%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Donald%20Trump%2C%20who%20has%20recently%20been%20elected%20for%20a%20second%20term%20as%20President%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%20has%20told%20House%20Republicans%20that%20he%20might%20consider%20a%20constitution-breaking%20third%20term%20in%20office.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-talks-of-constitution-breaking-3rd-term-as-president-details-here-7012449%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Display%20Names%2C%20Phone%20Numbers%3A%20Vendors%20At%20Delhi%20Vegetable%20Market%20Told%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EStreet%20vendors%20at%20a%20vegetable%20market%20in%20Delhi's%20Najafgarh%20will%20have%20to%20display%20their%20names%20on%20carts%20in%20a%20move%20the%20local%20councillor%20and%20the%20market%20association%20claimed%20was%20aimed%20at%20preventing%20%26quot%3Billegal%26quot%3B%20Bangladeshi%20and%20Rohingya%20migrants%20from%20selling%20produce%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20market%20association%20has%20also%20directed%20the%20vendors%20to%20display%20their%20phone%20numbers%20on%20nameplates%20on%20the%20carts%2C%20which%20will%20have%20a%20unique%20%26quot%3Bthela%20number%26quot%3B%20issued%20by%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20to%20implement%20this%20plan%20was%20made%20in%20a%20meeting%20of%20the%20market%20association%20with%20the%20local%20councillor%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20following%20complaints%20of%20unidentified%20sellers%2C%20suspected%20to%20be%20illegal%20migrants%20from%20Bangladesh%20and%20Myanmar%2C%20selling%20produce.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELocal%20BJP%20Councillor%20Amit%20Kharkhari%20said%20the%20move%20was%20not%20meant%20to%20discriminate%20against%20anyone%20or%20any%20particular%20community%20but%20for%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENazafgarh%20Vyapar%20Mandal%20President%20Santosh%20Rajput%20told%20PTI%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20asked%20all%20street%20vendors%20in%20the%20area%20to%20submit%20identity%20documents%20such%20as%20Aadhaar%20for%20verification.%26quot%3B%20This%20record%20will%20be%20maintained%20by%20the%20market%20association%20and%20submitted%20to%20the%20local%20police%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Municipal%20Corporation%20of%20Delhi%20(MCD)%20for%20security%20purposes%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20association%20said%20there%20were%20around%20300%20street%20vendors%20who%20sold%20farm%20produce%20in%20the%20market%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20plans%20to%20complete%20the%20verification%20process%20by%20November%2020%2C%20Rajput%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20this%20move%2C%20we%20aim%20to%20improve%20the%20system%20in%20the%20vegetable%20market.%20If%20the%20names%20and%20phone%20numbers%20of%20vendors%20are%20displayed%20on%20their%20carts%2C%20any%20buyer%20with%20a%20grievance%20can%20report%20it%20to%20us.%20This%20will%20also%20help%20us%20identify%20illegal%20migrants%20selling%20goods.%20We%20will%20forward%20their%20details%20to%20the%20MCD%20and%20the%20police%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnyone%20who%20does%20not%20have%20a%20nameplate%20will%20not%20be%20allowed%20to%20sell%20their%20produce%20in%20the%20market%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKharkhari%20said%20the%20decision%20to%20implement%20the%20action%20was%20taken%20unanimously%20by%20the%20market%20association%20and%20locals%20during%20a%20meeting%20at%20his%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20being%20done%20to%20discriminate%20against%20anyone%20or%20any%20particular%20community.%20This%20is%20just%20for%20security.%20We%20have%20received%20several%20complaints%20about%20unauthorised%20persons%20operating%20in%20the%20market.%20Keeping%20this%20in%20mind%2C%20the%20decision%20was%20made%20and%20is%20being%20implemented%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731517740000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2Fn46dqom_delhi-najafgarh_625x300_13_November_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdisplay-names-phone-numbers-vendors-at-delhis-najafgarh-vegetable-market-told-7012767%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Street%20vendors%20at%20a%20vegetable%20market%20in%20Delhi's%20Najafgarh%20will%20have%20to%20display%20their%20names%20on%20carts%20in%20a%20move%20the%20local%20councillor%20and%20the%20market%20association%2